-- Chinese Airlines Buy 102 Airbus Planes for $14 Billion During Hu's Visit
-- B y   G r e g o r y   V i s c u s i
-- 2010-11-04T17:48:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/chinese-airlines-buy-102-airbus-planes-for-14-billion-during-hu-s-visit.html
Four Chinese airlines signed
contracts to buy 102 Airbus planes for a total of $14 billion
during a state visit by President Hu Jintao to France. CASC, Air
China, China Eastern and China Southern bought 50 A320s, 42
A330’s and 10 A350’s, the French president’s office said in a
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gregory Viscusi at 
 gviscusi@bloomberg.net  